 how users navigate relationships between self-tracking technologies, social media, and everyday health management. .  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHealth attitudes. 0aHealthxSocial aspects. 0aSocial media. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152921015640uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529210163?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529210163423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529210163/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles